FBIS3-17894 "drsov061_b_94025" FBIS-SOV-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Seventy Percent of Armed Forces Not Paid in Mar LD2903211094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1836 GMT 29 Mar 94 LD2903211094 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] A critical situation emerged in the Russian Armed Forces as officers and warrant officers did not receive their salaries. INTERFAX learned from sources close to the Russian Defense Ministry that the Finance Ministry had set aside only 30 percent of the amount needed. Therefore, about 70 percent of officers and warrant officers were left without their pay for March. Many of them had not received their salaries for February either.
